The face-to-face engagement came after Her Majesty, 95, battled Covid in recent weeks, having spent three months under doctors' orders to only conduct light duties. She pulled out of the Commonwealth Day service on Monday due to issues over her comfort, it was said. The Queen was pictured in the Oak Room, standing without her walking stick as she congratulated Grace. The poet is being recognised for her work, including her 1983 debut collection I Is A Long-Memoried Woman. 